data.chText: 重量级拳击手（体重79.5公斤或以上）
data.enText: a boxer of the heaviest class in normal use, weighing 79.5 kilograms or more
a person or thing that weighs more than is usual

data.chText: 有影响力的人（或组织、事物）
data.enText: a very important person, organization or thing that influences others

word_means: 重量级拳击手(体重79.5公斤或以上)

means: 重量级拳击手(体重79.5公斤或以上)
有影响力的人(或组织、事物)

tr: a person of exceptional importance and reputation
a professional boxer who weighs more than 190 pounds
a wrestler who weighs more than 214 pounds
an amateur boxer who weighs no more than 201 pounds

value.def: A heavyweight is a boxer weighing more than 175 pounds and therefore in the heaviest class.
value.tran: （体重175磅以上的）最重量级拳击手

value.def: If you refer to a person or organization as a heavyweight, you mean that they have a lot of influence, experience, and importance in a particular field, subject, or activity.

example.tran: 爵士乐坛的重量级人物

value.tran: 重量级人物（或组织）;有影响力的人物（或组织）

trans: (体重为160至175磅的)轻重量级职业拳击手
